#!/bin/bash
yad --title="About Paper ENVIRONMENT" --window-icon="fedora-logo-icon" \
    --image="/usr/share/icons/hicolor/48x48/apps/fedora-logo-icon.png" \
    --width=600 --height=500 --center --button="Close:0" \
    --text-info --text-charset=utf-8 <<TEXT
Paper ENVIRONMENT is a collection of programs that together provide a full-featured desktop environment. The following programs are part of the Paper core:

Window Manager (jwm)
Handles the placement of windows on the screen and provides the taskbar.

Desktop Manager (pcmanfm --desktop)
Sets the background image and manages icons on the desktop.

File Manager (pcmanfm)
A lightweight file manager that is fast and easy to use.

Terminal Emulator (xterm / PaperTerminal)
The standard terminal window for running commands and modding.

Dialog Engine (yad / zenity)
Handles the popups, about windows, and interactive scripts.

Menu System (paper-menu-gen)
Automatically scans and organizes your installed applications.

-------------------------------------------------------
Owner and developer: Superchavo <superchavoofficialscratchyt@gmail.com>

The packages jwm, pcmanfm, xterm, and yad are distributed under the terms of the GNU General Public License as published by the Free Software Foundation; either version 2 of the License, or (at your option) any later version.
TEXT
